div.div:
All guardrails are enforced server-side before query execution. User-edited SQL is re-validated
through the same sanitize_sql() pipeline. This prevents SQL injection, data exfiltration, and
accidental table mutations. BigQuery cost caps (MAX_BYTES_BILLED) prevent runaway expenses.
